Christina Louise "Tina" Cullen MBE (born 1 March 1970 in Stockport, Cheshire) is a field hockey player from England.
Cullen has represented Great Britain in two consecutive Summer Olympics, starting in 1996 when the team finished in fourth place.She is player coach with Bowdon Hightown and has over 400 English Premier League goals to her name. She teaches sport at Greenbank High School and was appointed an MBE in the New Years honours list 2013.
